This paper deals with the application of machine learning and computer vision techniques for road detection, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) domains. The use of co-training, a semi-supervised learning approach, is a key aspect of the paper, which is a popular topic in machine learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of labeled and unlabeled data, which is a common theme in both artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL) research.
